<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1400,1651,1785]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sahlberg" authorityYear="1880" box="[189,433,1651,1677]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jenisseensis">
<emphasis box="[189,433,1651,1677]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Quedius jenisseensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a common arctoboreal Asian species, which has already been recorded from the 
<collectingRegion box="[189,248,1687,1713]" country="Russia" name="Altay" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Altai</collectingRegion>
Mountains in 
<collectingCountry box="[424,503,1687,1713]" name="Russia" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Salnitska M. &amp; Solodovnikov A." box="[520,910,1687,1713]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" pagination="1 - 100" refId="ref9088" refString="Salnitska M. &amp; Solodovnikov A. 2019 Rove beetles of the genus Quedius (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae) of Russia: a key to species and annotated catalogue. ZooKeys 847: 1 - 100. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 847.34049" type="journal article" year="2019">Salnitska &amp; Solodovnikov 2019</bibRefCitation>
). Based on the newly examined material here, we provide two new records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sahlberg" authorityYear="1880" box="[635,811,1724,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jenisseensis">
<emphasis box="[635,811,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Q. jenisseensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Kazakh part of 
<collectingRegion box="[1113,1175,1723,1749]" country="Russia" name="Altay" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Altai</collectingRegion>
. These are the first records of the species for 
<collectingCountry box="[491,628,1759,1785]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
and Middle Asia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
